Description.Text: A very pleasant hotel in the heart of London.

Located in a quiet side street in Mayfair, just off Piccadilly, this hotel is within easy reach of Park Lane, Regent Street, Oxford Street and some of London's best shopping. Five minutes away is Green Park underground station.

On average the rooms are small, but both the bedrooms and bathrooms are in very good condition. The bedrooms are decorated in a traditional style, with rich blues and pinks in the color scheme and traditional furniture. All bedrooms are air-conditioned.
This was formerly a terrace of Georgian houses, with leaded windows and a graceful red brick facade. The entrance is flanked by attractive plants.
The restaurant is located on the ground floor and again decorated in a traditional manner.
The lobby is small with wood paneled walls, Art Deco style lighting and an abundance of antique furniture and paintings all adding to its traditional character.
